          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. Eu paint market is of 5.37E+09kg (EUROPEAN COMMISSION 2002) of which 55% is paint and 35% is emulsion paint (http://www.psgdover.com/en/mouvex-paint-coatings-market-overview/what-are-paint-a-coatings/defining-paintaccessed, accessed 20151009). 22% is considered hazardous waste and 78% non hazardous waste (http://archive.epa.gov/sectors/web/pdf/paint_quantity_report.pdf, accessed 20151009). In the EU (Eurostat municipal waste treatment), of hazardous waste 23% is sent to hazardous incineration. Of non hazardous waste 23% is sent to incineration. 37% is considered to be sent to landfilling and it is split between sanitary and inert landfill using the same shares assumed for the US (see relevant dataset: “23% is sent to inert material landfill (http://archive.epa.gov/sectors/web/pdf/paint_quantity_report.pdf, accessed 20151009). The rest (65%) is considered to go to sanitary landfill.”) EUROPEAN COMMISSION (2002) STUDY ON HAZARDOUS HOUSEHOLD WASTE (HHW) WITH A MAIN EMPHASIS ON HAZARDOUS HOUSEHOLD CHEMICALS (HHC). Retrieved from: &lt;http://ec.europa.eu/environment/waste/studies/pdf/household_report.pdf&gt;, accessed 11th July 2016 Eurostat. Sustainable Development Indicator (SDI) on municipal waste Retrieved from: &lt;http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/web/waste/transboundary-waste-shipments/key-waste-streams/municipal-waste&gt;, accessed 11th July 2016</productionVolumeComment>
